The paper discusses a framework for private machine learning, which involves protecting the privacy of individual data points. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of logistic regression, which is a common machine learning algorithm (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of statistical methods to estimate the true underlying model, which falls under the category of data science (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of databases to store and manipulate data (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to perform machine learning (cs.AI).
